	<item>
		<title>By: Andy Ruff</title>
		<link>http://werblog.com/2005/07/ical-alternatives/#comment-47</link>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Andy Ruff]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Fri, 15 Jul 2005 02:56:54 +0000</pubDate>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://werbach.com/wordpress/?p=1241#comment-47</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[On Entourage:
- It does show your meeting locations in month/week/day view.
- All-day events display with the same limitation as iCal.
- You can customize the Entourage sounds but only via sound sets that require a bit of &quot;hacking&quot; to customize.
- The week view will give you a fuller view of each day (past 5PM).
- Compatibility with Outlook tends to be a bit better]]></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>On Entourage:<br />
&#8211; It does show your meeting locations in month/week/day view.<br />
&#8211; All-day events display with the same limitation as iCal.<br />
&#8211; You can customize the Entourage sounds but only via sound sets that require a bit of &#8220;hacking&#8221; to customize.<br />
&#8211; The week view will give you a fuller view of each day (past 5PM).<br />
&#8211; Compatibility with Outlook tends to be a bit better</p>
]]></content:encoded>
	</item>
